fields.description:
While testing CloudFormation and trying to start several instances simultaneously (via separate runInstances calls) I got the following error in the stack:

Caused by: org.postgresql.util.PSQLException: ERROR: duplicate key value violates unique constraint "uk_fxck35k7w28rv4t208pfp7x28"
  Detail: Key (metadata_unique_name)=(724132965308:default) already exists.
	at org.postgresql.core.v3.QueryExecutorImpl.receiveErrorResponse(QueryExecutorImpl.java:2161)
	at org.postgresql.core.v3.QueryExecutorImpl.processResults(QueryExecutorImpl.java:1890)

	at net.sf.hajdbc.invocation.SimpleInvoker.invoke(SimpleInvoker.java:53)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.invocation.AllResultsCollector$Invocation.call(AllResultsCollector.java:143)

	at net.sf.hajdbc.util.concurrent.SynchronousExecutor.invokeAll(SynchronousExecutor.java:175)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.util.concurrent.SynchronousExecutor.invokeAll(SynchronousExecutor.java:152)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.invocation.AllResultsCollector.collectResults(AllResultsCollector.java:81)

	at net.sf.hajdbc.invocation.InvocationStrategies.invoke(InvocationStrategies.java:35)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.invocation.LockingInvocationStrategy.invoke(LockingInvocationStrategy.java:59)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.sql.LocalTransactionContext$2.invoke(LocalTransactionContext.java:96)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.sql.AbstractInvocationHandler.invokeOnProxy(AbstractInvocationHandler.java:95)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.sql.AbstractInvocationHandler.invoke(AbstractInvocationHandler.java:85)
	at net.sf.hajdbc.sql.ChildInvocationHandler.invoke(ChildInvocationHandler.java:44)
	at com.sun.proxy.$Proxy161.executeUpdate(Unknown Source)
	at sun.reflect.GeneratedMethodAccessor222.invoke(Unknown Source)
	at sun.reflect.DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.invoke(DelegatingMethodAccessorImpl.java:43)
	at java.lang.reflect.Method.invoke(Method.java:606)
	at org.logicalcobwebs.proxool.ProxyStatement.invoke(ProxyStatement.java:100)
	at org.logicalcobwebs.proxool.ProxyStatement.intercept(ProxyStatement.java:57)
	at $java.sql.Wrapper$$EnhancerByProxool$$1f0fb793.executeUpdate(<generated>)
	at org.hibernate.engine.jdbc.internal.ResultSetReturnImpl.executeUpdate(ResultSetReturnImpl.java:133)
	... 97 more


There were other exceptions thrown after, but this is the root cause.  I was using AWS SWF which may run tasks in parallel so it is possible 4 instances were attempted to be launched at the same time.  I have worked around the issue in CloudFormation for now by synchronizing my calls, but the underlying error is in EC2.
fields.summary: Duplicate key constraint in EC2 if instances launched in quick succession/simultaneously

Failed insert attempts must be evicted from the session before attempting to find another free index.

The issue was concurrent attempts to create the extant network metadata for the security group. We now ensure the extant network info is loaded if it was created for another request.

To reproduce the issue, delete the security group to ensure it is not extant, then run multiple instances:

{code}
# euca-run-instances emi-eb5c8107 & euca-run-instances emi-eb5c8107 & euca-run-instances emi-eb5c8107 & euca-run-instances emi-eb5c8107 &
{code}

The reported issue occurred around one third of the time in my testing so multiple instance launches should be performed to verify the fix. 

The issue did not occur in EDGE or VPCMIDO modes.

I did not see any such errors when I attempted to launch instances simultaneously. It seem, the bug is fixed in 4.1 build.
